  "prompt": "Are there other movies like The Secret?",
  "response": "Yes, if you enjoyed \"The Secret,\" which focuses on the law of attraction and positive thinking, you might also like the following films and documentaries that explore similar themes of personal development, self-help, and the power of the mind:\n\n1. **What the Bleep Do We Know!?** (2004) - This film blends documentary and narrative elements to explore spirituality, quantum physics, and the effects of perception and thought on reality.\n\n2. **The Power of Intention** (2004) - Based on the teachings of Dr. Wayne Dyer, the film discusses how intention can influence your life and help manifest your desires.\n\n3. **The Law of Attraction: The Teachings of Abraham** (2006) - This film features Esther and Jerry Hicks and presents the principles of the law of attraction as taught by the non-physical entity Abraham.\n\n4. **Mindwalk** (1990) - Based on a conversation between three characters exploring themes of interconnectedness, thought, and reality, this philosophical film delves into how perception shapes our understanding of the world.\n\n5. **You Can Heal Your Life** (2007) - Based on Louise Hay's book, this documentary discusses the connection between thoughts, emotions, and physical health, offering insights into healing through positive affirmations and beliefs.\n\n6. **The Shift** (2009) - Featuring Dr. Wayne Dyer, this film discusses transitions in life and the importance of inner transformation to achieve fulfillment and happiness.\n\n7. **Heal** (2017) - This documentary explores the mind-body connection and how thoughts and beliefs can influence physical health and healing.\n\n8. **I Am** (2010) - Directed by Tom Shadyac, this documentary investigates questions about humanity and the universe, focusing on interconnectedness and positive thinking.\n\nThese films and documentaries encompass a range of topics related to self-improvement, spirituality, and the influence of mindset on personal experiences and outcomes.",
